''Under Illefarn'' was written by [[Steve Perrin]], with a cover by [[Jeff Easley]] and interior illustrations by [[Luise Perenne]], and was published by TSR in 1987 as a 48-page booklet with an outer folder.

While in development this module had the working title of ''Beneath Illefarn''. This name was made public by [[Jeff Grubb]] in [[Dragon magazine 119|''Dragon'' #119]]'s article "The Game Wizards."{{Cite dragon/119/The Game Wizards|59}}

The maps in this module have many numbered rooms that don't receive descriptions/fixed content anywhere in the text, leaving them to be populated by DMs.{{Cite dragon/161/Sage Advice|89}}

